    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-20T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="727"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d727">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 (Potsdam)/7–2045</note>
                <head>No. 727<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Proposal by the United States Delegation</hi>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content" calendar="gregorian"
                        when="1945-07-20">July 20, 1945</date>
                </dateline>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Declaration on Italy and Spain</hi>
                </p>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Proposal Presented to Foreign Ministers July</hi> 20,
                        1945<note n="1" xml:id="d727fn1">See <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref
                            target="#pg_147">p. 147</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>In the statement on the policy toward Italy introduced by the President on July
                        17<note n="2" xml:id="d727fn2">
                        <ref target="#d1089">Document No. 1089</ref>.</note> we propose that there
                    be included a statement to the effect that the Three Heads of Government will
                    support the entry of Italy into the United Nations Organization.</p>
                <p>The Three Heads of Government further declare that they will not support the
                    entry of Spain into the United Nations Organization, so long as Spain is under
                    the control of the present regime in that country.</p>
            </div>
